South Africa has recorded 1 736 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 686 891. The country has also recorded 160 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 17 408. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 160 more COVID-19 related deaths: “105 from KwaZulu-Natal, 13 from Gauteng, 18 from Eastern Cape, 6 from Free State, 6 from Limpopo, 4 from Mpumalanga and 8 from Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 339 686. The number of recoveries now stands at 618 771, this translates to a recovery rate of 90%.  4 339 686 686 891 618 771 50 712 17 408 636 179 As at 08 October 2020 21 172 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); 